children.subject: All of 12A is covered in the first lecture of 70. It is helpful for that content, but overall it's a very small portion of 70. Idk about GPA booster. My friend really liked it and did well but I thought it was some of the most boring stuff ever so I ended up doing pretty average. Also I took it with Professor Mancosu so idk about the other guys

history.content: Taking it right now. Learning the content is a cakewalk if you’ve taken 70, not really because of content overlap, but because you’ll already know how to think mathematically. HOWEVER, the weekly problem sets are long, tedious, and honestly feel like busy work, and they’re 45% of your grade so you can’t exactly blow them off. I would not recommend this class for that reason. ***ALSO IT WILL NOT SATISFY THE PHILOSOPHY BREADTH AS OF NEXT SEMESTER***
